    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are reading in the image file, or you have access to the code that reads in the file, know it is:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://docs.opencv.org/3.0-beta/modules/imgcodecs/doc/reading_and_writing_images.html#imread\" rel=\"noreferrer\">BGR</a> order if you used <code>cv2.imread()</code>   </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://matplotlib.org/api/image_api.html#matplotlib.image.imread\" rel=\"noreferrer\">RGB</a> order if you used <code>mpimg.imread()</code> (assuming <code>import matplotlib.image as mpimg</code>)  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you don't know how the file was opened, the <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/30802605/5411817\">accepted answer</a> <code>BufferedImage</code> is great for Java.<br>\nI would like to find a way to do the same in Python!</p>\n"
  } ],
