  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30802493/how-can-i-know-if-the-image-is-in-rgb-or-bgr-format",
  "title" : "How can I know if the image is in RGB or BGR format?",
  "body" : "<p>Is there any way to know in advance if an image used as an input to a system is in RGB or BGR format?</p>\n\n<p>I am using OpenCV with java API and I would like to convert an input image into grayscale or L*a*b* color space, but in OpenCV you have to specify first whether the image you want to convert is in RGB or BGR.</p>\n\n<p>The type of the image I am using is either <code>.jpg</code> or <code>.png</code>.</p>\n"
